		<pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2005 19:24:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1217#comment-22</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Kevin,  Totally agree on the importance of the Grokster case.  More attention was paid to the indecency issue, but this is where the real decision will be made about the future of (distributed) media and first amendment rights.  Without a positive ruling, cost of distribution for individuals will skyrockets and set the democracy in media movement back by a decade.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Kevin,  Totally agree on the importance of the Grokster case.  More attention was paid to the indecency issue, but this is where the real decision will be made about the future of (distributed) media and first amendment rights.  Without a positive ruling, cost of distribution for individuals will skyrockets and set the democracy in media movement back by a decade.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
