	<item>
		<title>By: smurfette</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2005/03/the-day-of-reckoning/#comment-21</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[smurfette]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 29 Mar 2005 17:21:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1217#comment-21</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Come on, let&#039;s go to Washingotn, and I&#039;m thinking of going to law school!

But I think given the previous case of Sony vs. Disney&amp;Universal, those poor tech software guys should be fine. And personally I find it most ridiculous and nonsense trying to put ban on the innocent technology or programming. It is the people or system(still manipulated by human) that is flawed. And it would be really disastrous if the Court came to the conclusion against innovation and technologically developmental freedom.

On the other one about cable guy vs. telco guy, I have no idea who should get what or how is that justified, although fair and free competition has always been at the mouth of everybody.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Come on, let&#8217;s go to Washingotn, and I&#8217;m thinking of going to law school!</p>
<p>But I think given the previous case of Sony vs. Disney&#038;Universal, those poor tech software guys should be fine. And personally I find it most ridiculous and nonsense trying to put ban on the innocent technology or programming. It is the people or system(still manipulated by human) that is flawed. And it would be really disastrous if the Court came to the conclusion against innovation and technologically developmental freedom.</p>
<p>On the other one about cable guy vs. telco guy, I have no idea who should get what or how is that justified, although fair and free competition has always been at the mouth of everybody.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
